The output should be an integer denoting the minimum possible value of the bitwise OR of the remaining elements of nums after applying at most k operations.



Input: nums = [1,1,2,2,3,4,4], k = 2
Output: 7
Explanation: We can apply the following operations:
1) [1,1,2,2,3,4,4] -> [1,1,2,4,3,4,4]
2) [1,1,2,4,3,4,4] -> [1,1,4,4,3,4,4]
The remaining array after applying the above operations is [1,1,4,4,3,4,4], which has a minimum bitwise OR of 7.



Note:

1 <= nums.length <= 10^5
1 <= nums[i] <= 10^9
1 <= k <= nums.length - 1














#[풀이]
class Solution {
    public int minOrAfterOperations(int[] nums, int k) {
        int ans = 0;
        int mask = 0;
        for (int b = 29; b >= 0; b--) {
            mask |= 1 << b;
            int cnt = 0;
            int and = -1;
            for (int x : nums) {
                and &= x & mask;
                if (and != 0) {
                    cnt++;
                } else {
                    and = -1;
                }
            }
            if (cnt > k) {
                ans |= 1 << b;
                mask ^= 1 << b;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}



